title: For Sale:  Rifle .458 SOCOM Rock River Arms
postcontent: This rifle is deer ready and has harvested its share of Indiana grown venison. It has lots of extras including FAB Defense GL-Shock, FAB Defense MWG Mag. Well Ext. Grip, Aftermarket Pistol Grip, extended charging handle. The RRA upper has had less than 100 rounds through it and it is very accurate. The scope is a Nikon Prostaff held in place by a M223 xr scope mount. It has worked perfectly for me. There are YouTube vids of people shooting deer at 450 yds. Far as I am concerned, out to 175-200 yards you are ethical (if you practice with it) but I would not go beyond that.   Three possible configurations: $1,199 with everything (except bipod) or $999 without the scope or mount or $749.00 for just the upper without scope or mount.  If you want the bipod, add $49.00.  If you want 20-25 rounds hand-loaded (Hornady FTX 325gr) add $50 to the price and I wll send them along. (The rounds are what made those holes in the paper and bigger holes in the deer I took this year and they are right.)   The target in the picture was shot just before deer season 2017 at 100 yrds under much less than optimal conditions. The top group are almost touching and the second group are within an inch and those were made at last light. This rifle hits where you aim.   NOTE: I will only ship to a FFL dealer and the shipping fees will be added to the cost of the rifle. I will not ship until I receive payment and payment clears. Money orders will be accepted but they will be checked. I have had buyer try to rip me off with very real looking money orders. Never had worked yet because I check them out. Not suspicious, but not stupid either. Most people are honest but this place seems to draw the other type so I am cautious. I will not ship until the money is in hand. If you are close by and want to see the weapon, I will meet you are our local police department and you can look all you want. No negotiating these prices. I am conflicted about selling this rifle as is and I have room in my safe for it and am not needing to sell it. If you don't think it is a fair price, understood but it is "my" price.   I am not a big fan of trading so I doubt I will be interested. If you have a really nice 7 mm Remington magnum rifle, maybe.

postcontent: Don't you think you deserve to treat yourself this Christmas? Here is your treat! Manufactured in May of 1943, this rifle has weathered 73 years quiet well.  All of the number identified parts of this rifle are Springfield Armory. Receiver (4/43-7/43), Bolt (10/44-12/44), Trigger Assembly (5/41-7/42), Hammer (9/40-6/42), Op rod (1/36-12/57), and Safety (10/40-7/41). Barrel is a Springfield Armory part but from 2/55. I hope I can load more than one or two pictures, because there shows no wear on any of the parts. If you are seriously interested I can email you pictures and part ID numbers. Package comes with rifle, sling, CMP hard case, manual, CMP Certificate of Authenticity, and 4 loaded enblocs. The picture of the muzzle explains why; the barrel looks new inside.  Muzzle wear is .5 and Throat wear at 3 out of 10, and Headspace checks good.  All measure well within spec.
